resume_text:
Jessica Williams
Marketing Manager

EXPERIENCE
Senior Marketing Manager | E-commerce Giant | 2020-Present
- Manage $5M annual marketing budget across digital channels
- Increased customer acquisition by 65% through optimized campaigns
- Led rebranding initiative resulting in 40% increase in brand awareness
- Built and managed team of 8 marketing specialists
- Improved email marketing ROI by 120% through A/B testing and segmentation
- Launched influencer program driving $2M in revenue

Marketing Manager | Fashion Retailer | 2018-2020
- Developed integrated marketing campaigns across social media, email, and paid ads
- Grew Instagram following from 50K to 300K in 18 months
- Managed relationships with 20+ agency partners
- Increased website traffic by 80% through SEO optimization
- Coordinated product launches with sales team

Marketing Coordinator | Startup Co | 2016-2018
- Created content for blog, social media, and newsletters
- Managed Google Ads campaigns with $50K monthly budget
- Analyzed campaign performance using Google Analytics
- Organized 10+ marketing events and webinars

SKILLS
Marketing: SEO/SEM, Content Marketing, Email Marketing, Social Media, Brand Strategy
Tools: Google Analytics, HubSpot, Mailchimp, Hootsuite, Canva, Adobe Creative Suite
Analytics: A/B Testing, Campaign Analytics, Customer Segmentation
Leadership: Team Management, Budget Management, Vendor Relations

EDUCATION
B.A. Marketing | Business University | 2016
Google Analytics Certification
HubSpot Inbound Marketing Certification
job_description: Seeking an experienced Marketing Manager to lead digital marketing efforts. Must have proven track record of managing large budgets, running multi-channel campaigns, and team leadership. Required: 5+ years marketing experience, proficiency with Google Analytics, SEO/SEM, email marketing platforms. E-commerce experience required.
